headline: AI Security Pivot Places Cisco Systems Stock (CSCO) in Pole Position
summary: Cisco Systems (CSCO) shares remained relatively flat despite the company surpassing expectations in its latest quarterly results published last week. The technology leader delivered both revenue and earnings beats, driven by strong performance in its security and observability segments. These results underscore Cisco’s continued transition from legacy networking hardware to a more diversified, higher-margin software and services portfolio.
